<emphasis box="[1294,1428,1028,1051]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Tetamauara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,243,1063,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Icupima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,243,1063,1086]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Icupima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[256,373,1063,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Iarucanga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[256,373,1063,1086]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Iarucanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[426,498,1062,1087]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[426,498,1062,1087]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), newly described. 
<taxonomicName box="[716,813,1062,1087]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[716,813,1062,1087]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycidola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[867,938,1062,1087]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[867,938,1062,1087]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were separated in the alternative of couplets “5” (translated): “Each elytron with 4 carinae… 
<taxonomicName box="[697,794,1098,1123]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[697,794,1098,1123]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycidola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ Each elytron with 2 carinae….. 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1248,1098,1123]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1176,1248,1098,1123]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.” They included 
<taxonomicName box="[151,267,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palliata">
<emphasis box="[151,267,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. palliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(type species), 
<taxonomicName box="[441,536,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batesi">
<emphasis box="[441,536,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. batesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[550,636,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beltii">
<emphasis box="[550,636,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. beltii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[650,771,1135,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="expansa">
<emphasis box="[650,771,1135,1158]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. expansa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[784,860,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felix">
<emphasis box="[784,860,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[874,1048,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavofasciata">
<emphasis box="[874,1048,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. flavofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[1108,1251,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulatrix">
<emphasis box="[1108,1251,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. simulatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1382,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1285,1382,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycidola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and also moving 
<taxonomicName box="[297,399,1172,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="togata">
<emphasis box="[297,399,1172,1195]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. togata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(type species), 
<taxonomicName authority="Waterhouse, 1880" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1880" box="[577,903,1170,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiqua">
<emphasis box="[577,692,1172,1195]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. antiqua</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Waterhouse" box="[701,903,1170,1195]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Waterhouse, C. O. (1880) New South-American Coleoptera, chiefly from Ecuador. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 5, 5, 285 - 302." type="journal article" year="1880">Waterhouse, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(transferred from 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson, 1868" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1112,1423,1170,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycaneptia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1112,1236,1172,1195]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycaneptia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson" box="[1243,1423,1170,1195]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Thomson, J. (1868) Materiaux pour servir a une revision des lamites (Cerambycides, coleopteres). Physis Recueil d' Histoire Naturelle, 2 (6), 146 - 200." type="journal article" year="1868">Thomson, 1868</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[151,291,1206,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isabellina">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. isabellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[355,481,1206,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycaneptia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barauna">
<emphasis box="[355,481,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. barauna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[518,589,1206,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[518,589,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Latter, Galileo &amp; Martins (2006) described 
<taxonomicName box="[1098,1285,1206,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="popeba">
<emphasis box="[1098,1285,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycidola popeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (2012) Novos taxons de Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) das Americas Central e do Sul. Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 102 (3), 331 - 339." type="journal article" year="2012">Martins &amp; Galileo (2012)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[465,564,1243,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[465,564,1243,1267]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">L. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,630,1555]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[358,667,1278,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Martins, U. R. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1991 a) Subdivisao do genero Lycidola Thomson, 1864 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Hemilophini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 35 (3), 553 - 565." type="journal article" year="1991" yearSuffix="a">Martins &amp; Galileo (1991a)</bibRefCitation>
, the prosternal process in 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1068,1278,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[971,1068,1278,1303]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycidola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is as wide as a procoxa, and in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,223,1314,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,223,1314,1339]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
1/3 the width of a procoxa. Evidently, they were talking about the central area of the prosternal process. However, the prosternal process in 
<taxonomicName box="[551,648,1350,1375]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[551,648,1350,1375]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycidola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although usually wider than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1016,1088,1350,1375]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1088,1350,1375]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is never as wide as a procoxa (
<figureCitation box="[159,316,1386,1411]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[205,1410,202,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[201,1417,196,1933]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12, Elytral apex (odd numbers) and ventral side of the prothorax (even numbers): 1 – 2, Lycidola batesi, female; 3 – 4, L. expansa, male; 5 – 6, L. flavofasciata, female; 7 – 8, L. simulatrix, female; 9 – 10, Apeba barauna, paratype female; 11 – 12, A. togata, female. 13 – 14, Lycidola popeba, holotype male: 13, dorsal habitus; 14, ventral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/438884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Figs 2, 4, 6, 8</figureCitation>
), and sometimes is slightly wider (
<figureCitation box="[710,778,1386,1411]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[205,1410,202,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[201,1417,196,1933]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12, Elytral apex (odd numbers) and ventral side of the prothorax (even numbers): 1 – 2, Lycidola batesi, female; 3 – 4, L. expansa, male; 5 – 6, L. flavofasciata, female; 7 – 8, L. simulatrix, female; 9 – 10, Apeba barauna, paratype female; 11 – 12, A. togata, female. 13 – 14, Lycidola popeba, holotype male: 13, dorsal habitus; 14, ventral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/438884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) than in 
<taxonomicName box="[878,949,1386,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[878,949,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[965,1138,1386,1411]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[205,1410,202,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[201,1417,196,1933]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12, Elytral apex (odd numbers) and ventral side of the prothorax (even numbers): 1 – 2, Lycidola batesi, female; 3 – 4, L. expansa, male; 5 – 6, L. flavofasciata, female; 7 – 8, L. simulatrix, female; 9 – 10, Apeba barauna, paratype female; 11 – 12, A. togata, female. 13 – 14, Lycidola popeba, holotype male: 13, dorsal habitus; 14, ventral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/438884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Figs 10, 12, 14</figureCitation>
). Thus, this feature cannot be used as a differential character.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,630,1555]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
We propose to redefine 
<taxonomicName box="[471,568,1458,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lycidola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[471,568,1458,1483]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Lycidola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having four carinae on each elytron (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1186,1458,1483]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[205,1410,202,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[201,1417,196,1933]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12, Elytral apex (odd numbers) and ventral side of the prothorax (even numbers): 1 – 2, Lycidola batesi, female; 3 – 4, L. expansa, male; 5 – 6, L. flavofasciata, female; 7 – 8, L. simulatrix, female; 9 – 10, Apeba barauna, paratype female; 11 – 12, A. togata, female. 13 – 14, Lycidola popeba, holotype male: 13, dorsal habitus; 14, ventral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/438884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Figs 1, 3, 5 7</figureCitation>
), with the second and third (from suture to outer side) fused at apical third (Y-shaped). 
<taxonomicName box="[884,956,1494,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Apeba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[884,956,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Apeba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is then comprised of species with just two or three elytral carinae (
<figureCitation box="[418,572,1530,1555]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[205,1410,202,1930]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[201,1417,196,1933]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 14. 1 – 12, Elytral apex (odd numbers) and ventral side of the prothorax (even numbers): 1 – 2, Lycidola batesi, female; 3 – 4, L. expansa, male; 5 – 6, L. flavofasciata, female; 7 – 8, L. simulatrix, female; 9 – 10, Apeba barauna, paratype female; 11 – 12, A. togata, female. 13 – 14, Lycidola popeba, holotype male: 13, dorsal habitus; 14, ventral habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/438884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Figs 9, 11, 13</figureCitation>
) and none fused.
</paragraph>
